# Responsive Design & Breakpoints

## Mobile-First Approach
- Design for smallest screen first (320px width minimum)
- Use Tamagui's breakpoint system: `$xs`, `$sm`, `$md`, `$lg`, `$xl`
- Test on multiple screen sizes regularly
- Progressive enhancement for larger screens

## Breakpoint Usage
```typescript
// ✅ Good - mobile-first responsive design
<XStack
  flexDirection="column"
  gap="$md"
  $sm={{ flexDirection: "row", gap: "$lg" }}
  $md={{ gap: "$xl" }}
>
  <Text 
    fontSize="$4" 
    $sm={{ fontSize: "$5" }}
    $md={{ fontSize: "$6" }}
  >
    Responsive Text
  </Text>
</XStack>

// ✅ Good - responsive layout with media queries
import { useMedia } from 'tamagui'

export function ResponsiveCard() {
  const media = useMedia()
  
  return (
    <YStack
      padding="$md"
      $xs={{ padding: "$sm" }}
      $lg={{ padding: "$xl" }}
      flexDirection={media.xs ? "column" : "row"}
      alignItems={media.xs ? "stretch" : "center"}
    >
      {/* Content */}
    </YStack>
  )
}
```

